pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. Here is the global goal to achieve:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Here is the public information about the environment:
{environment->public_information}
Here is what the vowel-capable agent reported (knowledge_vowel):
{knowledge_vowel}
Here is what the consonant-capable agent reported (knowledge_consonant):
{knowledge_consonant}
Using this information, produce a PDDL domain and a PDDL problem file that models the world (blocks, on-table, on, clear/top status), the movement rules (move only top blocks, one at a time), and the additional constraint that one agent can only move vowels and the other only consonants. Target the FastDownwards planner. Enclose the domain between <domain></domain> and the problem between <problem></problem>.
